{"url": "https://people.com/bodies/dirty-dancings-colt-prattes-weight-loss-matthew-mcconaughey-dallas-buyers-club/", "text": "Colt Prattes decided to follow an unconventional diet to prep for his role in the Dirty Dancing remake \u2014 one inspired by Matthew McConaughey\u2018s extreme weight loss plan to play an AIDS patient in Dallas Buyer\u2019s Club.\n\nPrattes \u2014 whose abs and love of weight lifting are well-documented on his Instagram \u2014 says he had to slim down to fit the look of the era.\n\n\u201cI actually had to lose about 20 to 30 lbs. for the movie because nobody was that big in the \u201960s,\u201d he told E! at the movie\u2019s PaleyLive premiere. \u201cI went on Matthew McConaughey\u2019s Dallas Buyer\u2019s Club diet as quick as I could.\u201d\n\nAnne Marie Fox/Focus Features/Everett\n\nPrattes, who took on Patrick Swayze\u2018s original role in the remake, says he found McConaughey\u2019s plan \u2014 which helped the actor drop 47 lbs. for his Oscar-winning role \u2014 on YouTube.\n\n\u201cHe said it\u2019s like, 8 oz. of fish in the morning, 8 oz. of fish at night, and all the red wine you can drink,\u201d Prattes says.\n\nMcConaughey explained his actual program on The Ellen DeGeneres Show in 2013.\n\n\u201cI met with two nutritionists first, so I found out how I could lose 2 to 3 lbs. a week,\u201d he told DeGeneres. And I had eight meals, but I had small meals. 5 oz. of fish, a couple of vegetables, a little something else three times a day and I also had my red wine at night to keep my head straight.\u201d\n\nFROM PEN: Half Their Size: The Weight Loss Stars Get Total Makeovers\n\nWhile Twitter users largely slammed the Dirty Dancing remake online, they were fans of Prattes \u2014 and his body.\n\nPrattes told PEOPLE that he was thrilled \u2014 but nervous \u2014 to step into Swayze\u2019s shoes for the iconic role.\n\n\u201cI couldn\u2019t try to be Patrick Swayze, he\u2019s Patrick Swayze. The man\u2019s a legend. I just wanted to love it and dance as hard as I could,\u201d Pratte said.", "images": ["https://people.com/thmb/c5p2bs9pUQO29RwnvYZm7iYKVzQ=/282x188/filters:no_upscale():max_bytes(150000):strip_icc():focal(809x246:811x248)/intermittent-fasting-3a459aca07c040838bb09c3823aae484.jpg", "https://people.com/thmb/Y1CN8rZN4kr7T_h_LobvRp7TKdw=/75x75/filters:no_upscale():max_bytes(150000):strip_icc()/J.Mazziotta2334-e3daa71fe1a745929e739c08e585253f.jpg", "https://people.com/thmb/Er_DAtfBIg_5nJ1PWZV0PolMmYs=/282x188/filters:no_upscale():max_bytes(150000):strip_icc():focal(299x0:301x2)/matthew-mcconaughey-1-600-304af45fd38d44558000fa29944243dd.jpg", "https://people.com/thmb/27NyYsvjAgwVMGdBmwB7zS6wL2M=/282x188/filters:no_upscale():max_bytes(150000):strip_icc():focal(749x0:751x2)/lexlee-hudson-3-4aa47286eac44830814cd3e1f2bdff3e.jpg", "https://people.com/thmb/1luutFLFJLXbYksk71lJPUzPE6Y=/282x188/filters:no_upscale():max_bytes(150000):strip_icc():focal(216x0:218x2)/kirstie-alley-2-435-e5fc7b210e444fd9a647a2a5d7b9c02e.jpg", "https://people.com/thmb/fY92vSsuJRSGXvTztwtpw2jon0Q=/282x188/filters:no_upscale():max_bytes(150000):strip_icc():focal(216x0:218x2)/matthew-mcconaughey-4-435-2-2f9480ad388b4d46a4e093a68976a548.jpg", "https://people.com/thmb/0LYMnB2Ko5KhuYVPOfEKPPENxbM=/282x188/filters:no_upscale():max_bytes(150000):strip_icc():focal(749x0:751x2)/al-roker-2-68dd50b17ecc48d9939cd5e96a36463f.jpg", "https://people.com/thmb/zU_YbPgNdZsuV1On8wJZILz3dvU=/282x188/filters:no_upscale():max_bytes(150000):strip_icc():focal(149x0:151x2)/matthew-mcconaughey-300-14-a6d0357adbde4b8f95f484e00f80f52f.jpg", "https://people.com/thmb/xC1O4US_8F-DYdLfGVppPvnSZ0c=/282x188/filters:no_upscale():max_bytes(150000):strip_icc():focal(999x0:1001x2)/shailene-woodley-adrift-1-2000-d8f98968f0be4a158ba41f81345218fb.jpg", "https://people.com/thmb/VqGf2h-ecU-xhxjxOAPH8C9R3Hg=/900x0/filters:no_upscale():max_bytes(150000):strip_icc():focal(634x0:636x2)/colt-prattes-2000-5d873df2bdab49e2bbb2ed0f54f63919.jpg", "https://people.com/thmb/gqx